<Base title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy policy for How To Win Capitalism">
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p>We collect the minimum personal data necessary to run the site and provide authentication.</p>

  <h2>What We Collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Account data: email, name, username, hashed password, role, profile details</li>
    <li>Session data: session token, created/expiry timestamps</li>
    <li>Security data: rate limit counters, lockout events, CAPTCHA results</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How We Use Data</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Authenticate you and keep you signed in</li>
    <li>Protect the service from abuse (rate limiting, CAPTCHA, honeypot)</li>
    <li>Provide profile and account management features</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>We use the following cookies:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>htwc_session</strong> — Authentication session cookie (httpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Strict). Expires after 24 hours.</li>
    <li><strong>htwc_consent</strong> — Remembers that you acknowledged our cookie notice. Expires after 1 year.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do <strong>not</strong> use advertising, analytics, or third-party tracking cookies.</p>

  <h2>Your Rights</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Access/Export: Request a copy of your account data</li>
    <li>Deletion: Request deletion of your account and associated data</li>
    <li>Correction: Update your profile information at any time</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data Retention</h2>
  <p>Account data is retained while your account remains active. Security logs (rate limits, lockouts) may be retained briefly for abuse prevention.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions or requests? Contact the site maintainer via the repository issues or provided support channels.</p>
</Base>
